snippet.textDisplay: Been listening Enter Shikari since TTTS and ever since it was my favorite band. When they released The Spark, i was a bit disappointed. Not because it was a bad album, i loved it, but because it wasn't the heavy Enter Shiakri I fell in love. Bought all of their albums, got few hoodies, even bought a vinyl player for the vinyls i bought. Now they dropped this song. Was really skeptical at first "Oh man, its gonna be another pop/rock song". But when i heard the intro, i was surprised. It felt so old school, it had that Enter Shikari signature sound. I was like "finally, another heavy song!!" And then chorus happend.... It was pretty disappointing. From pretty heavy to pop/rock stuff. I thought all hope was gone, and Enter Shikari no longer my favorite band.. BUT After i listened to it for 5-6 times, i fell in love with it and instantly pre-ordered album! Of course, i still miss the heavy stuff they used to make, but they grew older, I grew older, everyones music taste changed. They evolved, they changed, but i still love them and will continue to support them, as long as they make music! Thank you for making amazing and unique music <3
